assembleCopyOf

SupervisoryEvent assembleCopyOf(DESEvent event)
Assembles a new event with the same name and properties as the given event, which can then be added to the model. The event is not automatically added to the model.

Parameters:
event - the event whose properties are to be copied.
Returns:
As new SupervisoryEvent with the same name as the given event. If the given event is a SupervisoryEvent, the new event will have the same controllable and observable properties as the given event.

intersect

SupervisoryEventSet intersect(DESEventSet set)
Produce an event set which contains the intersection of this event set and the given event set.

The events in the intersection will be copies of the events in this event set. Thus, the method may be non-commutative in certain cases.

Specified by:
intersect in interface DESEventSet
Parameters:
set - the event set whose content will be used for the intersection
Returns:
the intersection of this event set and the given event set

union

SupervisoryEventSet union(DESEventSet set)
Produce an event set which contains the union of this event set and the given event set.

The events in the intersection will be copies of the events in this event set and copies of all the events in the given set which are not in this set. Thus, the method may be non-commutative in certain cases.

Specified by:
union in interface DESEventSet
Parameters:
set - the event set whose content will be used for the union
Returns:
the union of this event set and the given event set

subtract
